Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court orders a no contact and keep separate order with the co-defendants Brandon Branch and Leondre Durrah.

Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks not in court, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. appeared by video for Jahmir Dominique Banks.  Attorney Jennifer Jean Tate appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Case in court for bail motion. Bail motion by defense argued. Court reduces the cash bail to $20,000 cash. All other conditions remain in effect. Court further orders a no contact and keep separate order with the co-defendants Brandon Branch and Leondre Durrah. Case adjourned. Case remains calendared in Br 4.

Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. in court for Jahmir Dominique Banks.  Prosecuting attorney John J Rejowski in court for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for status conference. Defense informs the Court the defendant has filed a pro se bail motion. Court advises defendant bail motion cannot be heard as victim notification has not been made. Court advises the defendant bail motion will need to be heard at another date. Discussion held as to posture of the case. Defense requests final pre-trial and jury trial dates. Case remains calendared in Br 4.
Motion hearing scheduled for October 6, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Jury trial scheduled for January 3, 2023 at 08:30 am.
Defendant's Notice of Motion and Motion for Bail Reduction.  (Jahmir D. Banks, House of Correction, 8885 S 68th St, Franklin WI 53132).

Attorney Frederick F Klimetz in court, defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks not in court, in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for status conference. Discovery and offer received. Defense requests more time for review. State does not object. Case remains calendared in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for final pretrial. Defense advises of newly obtained discovery. Defense requests WITHDRAW SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND and adjournment of the jury trial. Court grants. Case adjourned in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for July 25, 2022 at 09:30 am.

Attorney Frederick F Klimetz in court, defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks not in court, in custody.  Michael Christopher Schindhelm appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Arguments heard as to bail. Court denies bail motion.   Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND.   Defense requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. Any witness lists, special jury instructions, and motion in limine to be filed by the final pretrial date. Any other motions must be filed by the final pretrial. Court further advises parties that after final pretrial date court will not accept any reduction of charges plea deal. Court orders case adjourned for final pretrial and jury trial in Branch 4.  Final pre-trial scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 03:00 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for July 25, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Notice and Motion to Reduce Bail
Branch 4 down on 5-11-2022. Parties contacted to reschedule hearing. Parties agree upon new court date. Case adjourned in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for June 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Filed: Original Transcript of PRELIMINARY HEARING  (29 pages) commencing 04-11-2022 by KATHERINE NELSON.

Attorney Frederick F Klimetz in court, defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks not in court, in custody.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court orders Atty Klimetz as counsel of record. Defense withdraws bail motion and request additional time for review. Case adjourned in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for May 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in court with Attorney Fred Richardson.  Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Detective M. Saavedra. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. Case is adjourned to Branch 04.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for April 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in court with attorney Fred Richardson.  Defendant Jahmir Dominique Banks in custody.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jahmir Dominique Banks appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Hanrahan, Branch 04. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
